cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.COMM, cs.MA 

The paper deals with interference mitigation in cellular-connected unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) communications, which involves wireless networking, communication theory, and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a cognitive radio-based solution, which involves spectrum sensing and allocation, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. Additionally, the paper deals with interference coordination, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.COMM (Communications and Networking). Finally, the paper uses numerical simulations to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed solution, which involves mathematical analysis and optimization, making cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) a possible category as well.
